Label: Month>Date Drill
Description: Drill-down dimension including Month and Date.

Label: User Name
Description: User Name as defined in the QMC (from the User Directory Connector)

Label: User Id
Description: Username of the individual performing an allocation change or accessing apps and using allocated tokens.

Label: Session Threshold
Description: Threshold of session counts (as defined as licensed sessions by a user). Use this to analyze how many users have met a session threshold in the selected timeframe. For example, select 4 in this field to see how many users have accessed Sense apps at least 4 times in the timeframe you have selected.

Label: Modified by
Description: UserId who made a change to license allocation.

Label: User Session Count
Description: Count of sessions (defined by licensed sessions) per user.

Label: Week - Day Drill
Description: Drill-down dimension including Week and Day.

Label: User Access Last Used
Description: The last time a user access Sense using an allocated pass.

QsdaVersion: Note: This does not include Login Access pass users."

Label: Timestamp
Description: Timestamp in the log file at which the activity ocurred.

Label: App Stream
Description: Stream into which an app is published.

QsdaVersion: 1) How a user accessed an app. For Token-based licensing: Login Access or User Access. For User-based licensing: Professional Access and Analyzer Access

Label: False
User Access Granted
Description: When User was granted access to a user access type (Professional, Analyzer, or User Token).

Label: Unified Licensing Product
Description: For customers enjoying Unified Licensing (QlikView + Qlik Sense), this dimension distinguishes which product was associated with the license consumption (Professional, Analyzer, or Analyzer Capacity)

Label: Change
Description: General type of activity performed, for example: Add, Update, or Delete for Login Access groups.

Label: App
Description: Name of the app that was accessed.

Label: Login Access Rule
Description: The Name of the Login Access Rule as configured in the QMC.
